bfasster

This is the beginning of a simpler rewrite of bfasst.

Usage:
It is expected that you copy the do files and the config and pregen
directories to your project.  The infrastructure expects to find each
design under a folder with the same name as the top level module.  The
configurable settings are found in the config directory.  src indicates
the folder containing all the projects (If missing this defaults to
'.').  part contains the part number for vivado.  synthargs contains
the parameters passed to synth_design in vivado, and vivadoargs contains
the args passed directly to vivado.

This can generate xdc, edif or checkpoint files.  Simply configure
properly and run:

redo <top-level>.xdc

or edif, or dcp.

Prereqs
redo (currently tested with apenwarr/redo)
	redo.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
